Interface IndexedListI<K,V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FunctionsI, I<K,V>, IndexedI<K,V>, IndexedIFunctions<K,V>, IndexedIFunctionsS<K,V>, IndexedIS<K,V>, ReadonlyIndexedI<K,V>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IndexedListIS<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    L, M, V2.LV2

    public interface IndexedListI<K,V>
extends IndexedIS<K,V>
    Adds a contract to work with sequential access to a IndexedIS. This interface makes no assumptions about the data structure's ordering. It is loosely inspired by some methods of List which may actually also fit a Map.
